New Records: Utah Jazz set season highs with 135 points, 35 assists, 16 3-pointers, and 60 points in the paint.
Key Match Events: Keyonte George scored 33 points and had nine assists, tying his career-high in points and setting a career-high with 13 free-throw attempts.
John Collins recorded a double-double with 28 points and 13 rebounds, also adding five assists.
Utah Jazz committed a season-low 12 turnovers.
Utah Jazz scored at least 30 points in each quarter, including a 40-point fourth quarter.
Pre-Game Insights: Utah Jazz entered the game with the 30th-ranked offense due to cold shooting and turnover struggles.
Post-Match Reflections: Keyonte George expressed that the team wanted to show they could compete at a high level and play the right way.
Jazz head coach Will Hardy praised the team's ball movement and execution on the offensive side.
Miscellaneous Highlights: John Collins' first-half poster dunk on Coby White.
Cody Williams contributed 11 points, five rebounds, and four assists, showcasing his ability to thrive around the basket.
